                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d516">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Currie</persName> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Cusack-Smith</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign Office</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-09-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 13, 1892</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Lord Rosebery is informed by the German
                    Government that it is the intention of the chief justice of Samoa to make the
                    requisition of land titles dependent on a previous survey, to be made at the
                    cost of the party interested.</p>
                <p>The German Government consider this proceeding to be unwarranted by the
                    provisions of the final act, and they are of opinion that it is unnecessary in
                    itself as <pb facs="0577" n="571" xml:id="pg_571"/> well as calculated to entail
                    undesirable delay and to throw disproportionate expense on the persons
                    concerned.</p>
                <p>The German consul at Apia will, accordingly, be instructed to inform the chief
                    justice that the German Government must withhold their sanction from the
                    measure.</p>
                <p>Her Majesty’s Government concur in the views of the German Government upon this
                    point, and I am to instruct you to act in concert with your German colleague in
                    any communications which it maybe necessary to make to the chief justice if he
                    should move further in the matter.</p>
                <p>I am,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. currie.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
